'''Mats Henrik Berne Wieffer''' (born 16 November 1999) is a Dutch professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]] or [[defensive midfielder]] for [[Premier League]] club [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands national team]].

==Club career==
=== FC Twente ===
Born in [[Borne, Overijssel|Borne]],<ref name="auto">{{Cite web |title=Mats Wieffer |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/person/pe545606/mats-wieffer/ |access-date=4 February 2021 |website=worldfootball.net}}</ref><ref name="auto1">{{Cite web |date=6 August 2018 |title=Mats Wieffer tekent bij FC Twente |url=https://www.borneboeit.nl/65095/nieuws/mats-wieffer-tekent-bij-fc-twente |access-date=4 February 2021 |website=Borne Boeit |language=nl}}</ref> Wieffer played youth football for RKSV NEO aged 5 before joining [[FC Twente]]'s academy at the age of 10.<ref name="auto1" /><ref>{{Cite web |title=Mats Wieffer |url=https://sbvexcelsior.nl/speler/mats-wieffer/ |access-date=4 February 2021 |website=sbvexcelsior.nl |publisher=SBV Excelsior |language=nl}}</ref> He made one [[Derde Divisie]] appearance for [[Jong FC Twente]] in the 2017–18 season,<ref name="auto" /> prior to making his professional debut for Twente on 30 October 2018 in a 4–2 [[KNVB Beker]] win over [[VV Noordwijk]], coming on a substitute for [[Aitor Cantalapiedra]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=31 October 2018 |title=Enthousiaste FC Twente-debutant Wieffer op een roze wolk: "Een fantastische dag" |url=https://www.rtvoost.nl/nieuws/301372/Enthousiaste-FC-Twente-debutant-Wieffer-op-een-roze-wolk-Een-fantastische-dag |access-date=4 February 2021 |website=RTV Oost |language=nl}}</ref> He made his league debut in a 2–0 win over [[TOP Oss]] in March 2019.<ref>{{soccerway|mats-wieffer/576067|accessdate=4 February 2021}}</ref> FC Twente were promoted to the [[Eredivisie]] as champions of the [[2018–19 Eerste Divisie|Eerste Divisie]] in the same season, but Wieffer did not appear for FC Twente's first team in the [[2019–20 FC Twente season|2019–20 season]].

=== Excelsior ===
In June 2020, Wieffer joined [[Excelsior Rotterdam|Excelsior]] on a free transfer, signing a three-year contract with the club.<ref>{{Cite web |date=30 June 2020 |title=Mats Wieffer na tien jaar van FC Twente naar Excelsior: "Mooie tijd geweest" |url=https://www.rtvoost.nl/nieuws/332631/Mats-Wieffer-na-tien-jaar-van-FC-Twente-naar-Excelsior-Mooie-tijd-geweest |access-date=4 February 2021 |website=RTV Oost |language=nl}}</ref> He made his debut for Excelsior on 29 August 2020, replacing [[Mitchell van Rooijen]] in a 1–6 win against [[Jong PSV]] in the [[2020–21 Eerste Divisie|Eerste Divisie]]. He was sent off with a red card in the league game against [[FC Eindhoven]] on 9 October 2020 (1–1). On 5 February 2021, Wieffer scored his first goal in professional football in a 0–2 win against [[FC Volendam]]. He was named Excelsior Player of the Year after his first season at the club, winning 26% of the votes.<ref>{{Cite web |date=13 May 2021 |title=Mats Wieffer verkozen tot Pro Excelsior speler van het jaar |trans-title=Mats Wieffer chosen Pro Excelsior player of the year |url=https://excelsiorrotterdam.nl/2021/05/mats-wieffer-verkozen-tot-pro-excelsior-speler-van-het-jaar/ |access-date=23 July 2024 |website=Excelsior Rotterdam |language=nl}}</ref> On 29 May 2022, he scored in the [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]] as Excelsior beat [[ADO Den Haag]] in the final of the [[2021–22 Eerste Divisie#Promotion/relegation play-offs|play-offs]] to promote to the Eredivisie

=== Feyenoord ===
In June 2022, Wieffer moved to [[Feyenoord]] on a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/arnesen-blij-met-komst-wieffer-hij-is-uit-het-juiste-hout-gesneden |title=Arnesen blij met komst Wieffer: 'Hij is uit het juiste hout gesneden |language=Dutch |date=23 June 2022 |access-date=23 June 2022}}</ref> After getting injured in a friendly against [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]] in pre-season,<ref>{{Cite web |date=9 July 2022 |title=Feyenoord wint van Oostenrijkse kampioen, maar ziet Mats Wieffer op brancard veld verlaten |trans-title=Feyenoord wins against Austrian champion, but sees Mats Wieffer leave the pitch on stretcher |url=https://www.ad.nl/nederlands-voetbal/feyenoord-wint-van-oostenrijkse-kampioen-maar-ziet-mats-wieffer-op-brancard-veld-verlaten~a9476948/ |access-date=23 July 2024 |website=Algemeen Dagblad |language=nl}}</ref> he made his debut for Feyenoord and in European football on 8 September 2022, coming on as a substitute for [[Javairô Dilrosun]] in a 4–2 defeat against [[SS Lazio|Lazio]] in the [[2022–23 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]]. Three days later, he replaced Dilrosun during a 3–0 victory against [[Sparta Rotterdam]] to make his Eredivisie debut. On 13 January 2023, Wieffer scored his first goal for the club while also providing an assist in a 3–1 cup win over [[PEC Zwolle]], what was his first start for the club.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/extra-defensieve-zorgen-smetje-op-bekerwinst-van-feyenoord |title=Extra defensieve zorgen smetje op bekerwinst van Feyenoord |work=Voetbal International |trans-title=extra defensive worries blemish Feyenoord's cup win |date=12 January 2023 |access-date=12 January 2023}}</ref> He was named Feyenoord Player of the Month for January 2023 and February 2023.<ref name="Jan 2023">{{cite web |url=https://www.feyenoord.nl/nieuws/nieuwsoverzicht/mats-wieffer-speler-van-de-maand-110223 |title=Wieffer verkozen tot eerste Legioen Speler van de Maand in 2023 |trans-title=Wieffer chosen first Legioen Player of the Month in 2023 |publisher=Feyenoord |language=Dutch |date=11 February 2023 |access-date=27 April 2024}}</ref><ref name="Feb 2023">{{cite web |url=https://www.feyenoord.nl/nieuws/nieuwsoverzicht/twee-persoonlijke-prijzen-voor-mats-wieffer-170323 |title=Twee persoonlijke prijzen voor Mats Wieffer |trans-title=Two personal awards for Mats Wieffer |publisher=Feyenoord |language=Dutch |date=17 March 2023 |access-date=27 April 2024}}</ref> On 13 April 2023, Wieffer scored his first goal in a European club competition, scoring the only goal in a 1–0 win over [[AS Roma]] in the [[2022–23 UEFA Europa League knockout phase#Quarter-finals|quarter-finals]] of the UEFA Europa League.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/wieffer-laat-de-kuip-ontploffen-met-europese-primeur |title=Wieffer laat De Kuip ontploffen met Europese primeur |trans-title=Wieffer makes De Kuip explode with his first European goal |date=13 April 2023 |access-date=14 April 2023}}</ref> He assisted goals of [[Oussama Idrissi]] and [[Igor Paixão]] on 14 May 2023 as Feyenoord beat [[Go Ahead Eagles]] 3–0 to secure its sixteenth Eredivisie title.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2475118-feyenoord-verslaat-go-ahead-en-is-na-zes-jaar-weer-kampioen-van-nederland |title=Feyenoord verslaat Go Ahead en is na zes jaar weer kampioen van Nederland |trans-title=Feyenoord beats Go Ahead and is champions of the Netherlands against after six years |date=14 May 2023 |access-date=23 July 2024 |language=nl}}</ref>

On 4 August 2023, Wieffer played the full game as Feyenoord lost the [[2023 Johan Cruyff Shield|Johan Cruyff Shield]] 0–1 to [[PSV Eindhoven]]. Wieffer made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut on 19 September 2023, in a 2–0 win against [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]. He scored his first goal in the competition on 28 November 2023, during a 1–3 defeat against [[Atlético Madrid]]. Ahead of the [[2024 KNVB Cup final|KNVB Cup final]] on 21 April 2024, Wieffer suffered a thigh injury, ruling him out for the remainder of the season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.feyenoord.com/nl/news/medische-update-mats-wieffer-030524 |title=Medische update Mats Wieffer |trans-title=Medical update Mats Wieffer |date=3 May 2024 |access-date=23 July 2024 |language=nl}}</ref> Feyenoord went on beat [[NEC Nijmegen|NEC]] 1–0 in the cup final and finish in second place in the [[2023–24 Eredivisie|Eredivisie]]. During his time at Feyenoord, Wieffer played 54 league games, in which Feyenoord averaged 2.52 points, recording a joint-record for players in the Eredivisie with over 50 games played.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://x.com/OptaJohan/status/1808818422123278727 |title=2.52 – Mats Wieffer averaged 2.52 points per Eredivisie game, no Dutch player (min. 50 games) recorded a better average in the league's history. Talisman. |date=4 July 2024 |access-date=23 July 2024}}</ref>

=== Brighton and Hove Albion ===
On 5 July 2024, Wieffer joined [[Premier League]] club [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]], signing a contract until June 2029.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Wieffer joins Albion from Feyenoord |url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/4052325/wieffer-joins-albion-from-feyenoord |access-date=2024-07-05 |website=brightonandhovealbion.com |archive-date=5 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240705221359/https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/4052325/wieffer-joins-albion-from-feyenoord |url-status=dead }}</ref> With a reported fee of €30&nbsp;million, it became Feyenoord's most expensive outgoing transfer of all-time.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nu.nl/voetbal/6319593/wieffer-lost-kokcu-af-als-duurste-uitgaande-feyenoord-transfer-ooit.html |title=Wieffer lost Kökçü af als duurste uitgaande Feyenoord-transfer ooit |trans-title=Wieffer replace Kökçü as the most expensive outgoing Feyenoord transfer ever |date=6 July 2024 |access-date=23 July 2024 |language=nl}}</ref> He made his Premier League debut in Brighton's opening match against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] on 17 August 2024, where he'd register an assist as the Seagulls would go on to win 3–0.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/everton-brighton-and-hove-albion/FsY | title=Everton vs Brighton & Hove Albion live score, H2H and lineups &#124; Sofascore }}</ref> On 11 April 2026 he scored two goals in a game for the first time in his career as Brighton won 2-0 at [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Unwin |first=Will |date=2026-04-11 |title=Mats Wieffer doubles up as Brighton push Burnley closer to the drop |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2026/apr/11/burnley-brighton-premier-league-match-report |access-date=2026-04-13 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref>

==International career==
On 17 March 2023, Wieffer received his first call-up to the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands senior national team]] for the [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying|Euro 2024 qualifying]] matches against [[France national football team|France]] and [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/nieuws/nederlands-elftal/80692/koeman-roept-drie-debutanten-op |title=Koeman roept drie debutanten op |trans-title=Koemans includes three debutants |language=Dutch |date=17 March 2023 |access-date=17 March 2023}}</ref> He made his debut on 27 March as a starter in a 3–0 win over Gibraltar.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/oranje-neemt-twijfels-niet-weg-met-pover-optreden-tegen-gibraltar |title=Oranje neemt twijfels niet weg met pover optreden tegen Gibraltar |trans-title=Netherlands doesn't take away doubts after poor showing against Gibraltar |language=Dutch |date=27 March 2023 |access-date=27 March 2023}}</ref> On 21 November 2023, Wieffer scored his first senior international goal in the Netherlands' 6–0 win against Gibraltar.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hincks |first1=Michael |title=Gibraltar 0–6 Netherlands: Calvin Stengs Scores Hat-Trick as Dutch Sign Off Qualifying in Style with Thumping Win |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/euro-qualifying/2024/gibraltar-v-netherlands-euro-2024-qualifying-live_sto9890396/story.shtml |access-date=22 November 2023 |work=Eurosport |date=21 November 2023}}</ref> A thigh injury ruled him out from participating in [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2520743-koeman-maakt-voorselectie-ek-bekend-geen-zirkzee-geen-wieffer |title=Koeman maakt voorselectie EK bekend: geen Zirkzee, geen Wieffer |trans-title=Koeman announces preliminary squad Euros: no Zirkzee, no Wieffer |date=16 May 2024 |access-date=23 July 2024 |language=nl}}</ref>

== Style of play ==
Wieffer said that he prefers to play as a [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|number six]], but is also able to play [[Midfielder#Box-to-box midfielder|box-to-box]]. He has been praised for his mentality, interceptions, passing and energy and called "the missing link between Feyenoord's offence and defence."<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/modals/en/media-article-popup/mft-news-interviews-mats-wieffer-lowdown |title=The Lowdown On Mats Wieffer |website=Brighton & Hove Albion |date=18 July 2024 |access-date=24 July 2024}}</ref> In the [[2023–24 Eredivisie]], Wieffer ranked highly for blocks, interceptions, ball recoveries and tackles. He was compared to [[Moisés Caicedo]] and [[Alexis Mac Allister]] after his transfer to [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]].<ref>{{cite web |first1=Duncan |last1=Alexander |first2=Andy |last2=Naylor |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5616704/2024/07/09/mats-wieffer-brighton-transfer/ |title=What Mats Wieffer will bring to Brighton: An all-rounder to boost a post-Caicedo and Mac Allister midfield |website=The Athletic |date=9 July 2024 |access-date=24 July 2024}}</ref> Since April of [[2024–25 Brighton & Hove Albion F.C. season|Brighton's 2024–25 Premier League campaign]], Wieffer has been most frequently deployed as a [[right-back]] by head coach [[Fabian Hürzeler]], a position he quickly grew accustomed to as he ranks in the 95th percentile of right-backs for tackles won and clearances during the [[2025–26 Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web |first1=Andy |last1=Naylor |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/7122503/2026/03/17/brighton-mats-wieffer-right-back-midfield/ |title=Brighton’s Mats Wieffer says he prefers playing in midfield rather than at right-back |website=The Athletic |date=17 March 2026 |access-date=17 March 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first1=Harry |last1=Edwards |url=https://www.squawka.com/en/features/position-ranking-premier-league-best-right-backs-right-now/ |title=The best Premier League right-backs in 2025-26 |website=Squawka |date=16 March 2026 |access-date=17 March 2026}}</ref>

